snippet.textDisplay: Taiwan has been absolutely outstanding, largely because they didn’t trust the PRC (China) and are not in the WHO (which didn’t bother to quality check China’s data, “cough” lies). New Zealand followed Taiwan’s strategy early on and now have a similarly impressive low rate. If more countries listened to Taiwan in the early days they would have been in the same excellent position as Taiwan is now as the country with the worlds most successful Covid strategy.
